<p align=center style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:center'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p align=center style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:center'>The <i>Create Test
Bench</i> <span class=GramE>window<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>will</span>
appear:</p>

<p align=center style='margin-left:.25in;text-align:center'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1026" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:207.75pt;height:224.25pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="Creating_TB_files/image003.jpg" o:title="testbench2"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=277 height=299
src="Creating_TB_files/image003.jpg" v:shapes="_x0000_i1026"><![endif]></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
auto;margin-left:.5in;text-align:center'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>

<p style='margin-left:.5in'>After clicking <i>OK</i>, the <b>Design Browser</b>
window will contain a new component called <i>ALU_tb</i> with a Block Diagram
view alread created. Open <i>ALU_tb</i> to see a design similar to Figure 2. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
auto;margin-left:.5in;text-align:center'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="_x0000_i1027"
 type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:667.5pt;height:444pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="Creating_TB_files/image005.gif" o:title="image005"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=890 height=592
src="Creating_TB_files/image005.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_i1027"><![endif]></p>

<h4 align=center style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:center'>Figure 2</h4>

<p style='margin-left:.5in'>Resize and rearrange the two blocks so that it is
more readable, as in Figure 3. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:
auto;margin-left:.5in;text-align:center'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="_x0000_i1028"
 type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:593.25pt;height:360.75pt'>
 <v:imagedata src="Creating_TB_files/image006.gif" o:title="image007"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=791 height=481
src="Creating_TB_files/image006.gif" v:shapes="_x0000_i1028"><![endif]></p>

<h4 align=center style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:center'>Figure 3</h4>

<p style='margin-left:.5in'>Notice that the signals that are output from your
design component (in green) have the same name as those which are input into
the sub-block called <i>ALU_tester</i> and vice-versa. We have not seen this
before, but another feature of the <i>Block Diagram Editor</i> is that signals
of the same name are the same signal, even if they are not visually connected
together.</p>

<p style='margin-left:.5in'>Now, lets being to design the ALU_tester block,
descend into this block by clicking on it and selecting a block diagram view
from <span class=GramE>the create</span> new view panel. </p>

<p align=center style='margin-left:.5in;text-align:center'><a
href="ALU_Tester.html">Click here to proceed.</a></p>

